== 类似天体活动 ==
{{Main article|掠地火球}}
流星体经常闯入地球大气层，但人类很少录下高层大气的掠地天体<ref name="IAU">{{cite web | url = http://neo.ssa.esa.int/web/guest/neo-chronology | title = Near Earth Asteroids (NEAs): A Chronology of Milestones 1800 – 2200 | author = Karel A. van der Hucht | date = 2021-01-01 | publisher = European Space Agency | access-date = 2021-01-05 | archive-date = 2021-01-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210121123359/http://neo.ssa.esa.int/web/guest/neo-chronology | dead-url = no }}</ref>。获得验证的第一个可靠记录流星体应该是[[1860年大流星|1860年7月20日]]掠过美国纽约州上空<ref name="TSU">{{cite web | website = University News Service | publisher = Texas State University | access-date = 2021-01-05 | url = https://www.txstate.edu/news/news_releases/news_archive/2010/06/YearOfMeteors060110.html | title = Texas State astronomers solve Walt Whitman meteor mystery | last = Blaschke | first = Jayme | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201127180219/https://www.txstate.edu/news/news_releases/news_archive/2010/06/YearOfMeteors060110.html | date = 2010-05-28 | archive-date = 2020-11-27 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。部分文献把1990这次发现与1972年白日大火球相提并论<ref name="WGN" />，后者掠过美国[[犹他州|犹他州]]和加拿大[[艾伯塔省|艾伯塔省]]，是人类科学观察和研究的第一个掠地火球<ref name="IAU" />。1972年的流星体质量比1990年这枚要大上千倍，近地点比1990年流星体近四十公里<ref name="WGN" />。科学家利用两次观测所获数据开发计算掠地火球轨迹的方法，此后用来计算2006年3月29日掠过日本上空的流星体轨迹<ref name="EPSC">{{cite conference | first1 = S. | last1 = Abe | first2 = J. | last2 = Borovička | first3 = P. | last3 = Spurný | first4 = P. | last4 = Koten | first5 = Z. | last5 = Ceplecha | author6 = Meteor Network Team in Japan | title = Earth-grazing fireball on March 29, 2006 | booktitle = European Planetary Science Congress 2006 | pages = 486 | date = 2006-09-18–22 | location = Berlin | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190528072728/http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu/full/conf/epsc./2006//0000486.001.html | url = http://articles.adsabs.harvard.edu/full/conf/epsc./2006//0000486.001.html | bibcode = 2006epsc.conf..486A | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2019-05-28 | accessdate = 2021-01-05 }}</ref>。

